article.headline: Northwestern St. 92, McNeese State 73
article.story: LAKE CHARLES, La. (AP) -- Tramaine Hancock scored 21 points and Jermaine Wallace 15 to lead Northwestern State to a 92-73 victory over McNeese State on Saturday night. Tyronn Mitchell added 11 points and Colby Bargman 10 for Northwestern (12-11, 6-3 Southland Conference), which led 42-35 at halftime. Troy Aaron led McNeese (7-13, 2-7) with 17 points, while Edward Garriet added 15 points. Northwestern finished with a 45-38 edge in rebounding and also shot better from the field, 51.8 percent to 36 percent. <
